woods:
    play sound click
    if $data.ghost.foundDeepCave:
        choice:
            "The Seventh City is nearby. You know it. Perhaps it is time to let The Simmer know you know it too?"
            "[Let The Sinner know you know] <span class='prompt'>[[-1 ACTION]]</span>" if (>= $stats.actions.value 2):
                play sound spendAction
                set data.game_map.inMap false
                add_stat actions -1
                set_button button_woods false
                run transition_black woods_sinner
                clear_dialog
            "<span class='prompt'>[[BACK]]</span>":
                jump game_map
    else:
        choice:
            "The Sinner has agreed on a little foray into the woods. How could one miss such an opportunity?"
            "[One simply could not] <span class='prompt'>[[-1 ACTION]]</span>" if (>= $stats.actions.value 2):
                play sound spendAction
                set data.game_map.inMap false
                add_stat actions -1
                set_button button_woods false
                run transition_black woods_sinner
                clear_dialog
            "<span class='prompt'>[[BACK]]</span>":
                jump game_map

    play ambient amb_forest 1
    "The Sinner leans against a fence post. She is facing away from you, looking north."
    "The smoke from her cigarette mingles with the morning fog. It rolls in from North Acres and the barrows upon Watership this time of year. A blanket of ghosts drowning the lands they once ruled."
    clear_dialog
    talk sinner talk "You live near the woods, don't you, Ghost?"
    clear_dialog
    "She does not turn to look at you. Some mushrooms have caught her eye. Such small things. She steps on one, and spores puff from its dome. She watches them dissipate into the cold air."
    if (roll woods_smell_lovely lovely 40):
        talk lovely talk "Such a perceptive woman! You smell of leaves and daffodil pollen and sheep and moss."
        talk lovely talk "Among other things, of course, but she can pick these out quite distinctively. The scent of a woodland dweller."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    talk sinner talk "Shall we march onwards?"
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "She starts to march onwards. Evidently it was a rhetorical question. The real question will come later."
        "[March onwards]":
            clear_dialog
            "The background hum of birdsong. <span class='writtenText'>'Piep piep piep!'</span>, <span class='writtenText'>'Pip pip pip!'</span>. Even an ever so faint <span class='writtenText'>'peep. peep. peep. peep. peep. peep. peep. peep.'</span> followed by an unpleasant record scratch."
            clear_dialog
            "The rustling of golden leaves."
            "Signposts engulfed in tree trunks."
            "Forgotten bird skulls."
            "Weird mushrooms."
            "The smell of dirt."
            "A caterpillar crawling along."
            "The softness of the ground."
            "The way the roots form stairs."
            if $data.raven.goodEnd:
                "Down a path you do not take, a Ratzubishi, left in her namesakes favourite spot. Between the bluebells and the oak tree."
            "Are the woods your true home?"
            clear_dialog
            "No. But perhaps they should be?"
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk sinner talk "You seem happy, Ghost. The woods suit you?"
        "\\"I LIKE the woods.\\"":
            talk sinner talk "Mmm. They have their charm don't they. Earthy undertones, a hint of... is that cocoa?"
            if (roll woods_coco_lovely lovely 60):
                talk lovely talk "She misses cocoa."
                if (roll woods_cocoa_orb orb 20):
                    talk orb talk "The global supply chain has yet to fully recover from the war."
                    talk orb talk "The cocoa supplying islands in The American Sea still suffer from the tail end of the rabies pandemic. The cargo vessels that deliver their tasty bounty sunk during the war and yet to be rebuilt."
                else:
                    wait 1000
            else:
                wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    talk sinner talk "When the city and her smokestacks and her teeth and her sins disappear behind the treeline it is easy to forget it was there at all, isn't it?"
    clear_dialog
    "A bit of litter flies through the air. A pamphlet. <span class='writtenText'>'MOUNT BLUEHILLS! OPENING NEXT WEEK!'</span>"
    clear_dialog
    talk sinner talk "Ah. Well. Nevertheless, the woodland air clears the mind, if nothing else."
    clear_dialog
    "She taps some ash from the end of her cigarette."
    clear_dialog
    play sound clothing
    choice:
        "The Sinner stops walking and leans against a tree, gazing up into the orange canopy. A butterfly lands on her nose. It's rare to see them this time of year. The Sinner goes cross eyed staring at it, and then it is gone."
        "[Lean next to her] \\"You stopped walking. Did you forget how to walk? I can show you if you want?\\" [Take a few big steps back and forth] \\"Like that.\\"":
            play sound clothing
            "She smiles, if only briefly. Her face quickly returns to its natural, dour state."
            clear_dialog
            talk sinner talk "No, I just need a rest."
        "[Lean next to her normal style]":
            play sound clothing
            run skip
    clear_dialog
    "The moss cushions you. Sticks to your coat. Makes it kind of green and dirty. It's nice. This is how we're meant to live. Scrungling in the trees, naked and free..."
    if $data.global.writerNaked:
        clear_dialog
        talk orb talk "Keep your clothes on please. You'll catch your death of cold if you strip off out here."
    jump woods_menu

woods_menu:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "The Sinner lights a cigarette. A wood pigeon sits above you in the canopy and sniffs up the smoke."
        "\\"Why are you so sleepy, sleepyhead?\\"" if (!= $data.woods.sinChat true):
            set data.woods.sinChat true
            talk sinner talk "I slept badly, troubled."
            clear_dialog
            talk sinner talk "The same dream. The same dream again..."
            talk sinner talk "Inescapable. This is the truth of the world, Ghost."
            talk sinner talk "It is evil, only evil. It strips of us the light of creation with its cruelty until sin is all that remains. The souls is gone, everything is gone. Only your sin remains, hanging over your head for the raven to see."
            talk sinner talk "You forget about it. Or you ignore it. You don't see it, that's for sure. But I *have*. I have seen *it*."
            clear_dialog
            "She gestures vaguely, and at nothing."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk sinner talk "My sins are too numerous to count... burning the coal that murdered my town, is going to murder all of us..."
                "\\"I don't think you should beat yourself up for using coal. You need to stay warm and toasty somehow, don't you? Otherwise your toes will get cold...\\"":
                    talk sinner talk "Staying warm in the short term by murdering the future. Insanity."
                    clear_dialog
                    "She looks at your bemused face and snorts."
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk sinner talk "What? You think all of that coal dust floats harmlessly off into the sky and disappears? No, Ghost, it flies high above our heads, and blocks out the sun. If we keep burning coal we will soon all freeze."
                        "\\"Holy crackers, really?\\"":
                            talk sinner talk "Really."
                            if (roll woods_coal_orb orb 60):
                                talk orb talk "Wrong, but go off I guess."
                            else:
                                wait 1000
                                clear_dialog
                                "She says it with such emphasis on the full stop that it sounds utterly without doubt."
                        "\\"Hmm. I'm not convinced. It's been snowing for many many centuries already.\\"":
                            talk sinner talk "Soon there will be no need for the word <span class='writtenText'>'snowing'</span>. The snow will be the air we breath. The ground we trudge through. We have not a word for 'there is air', for always it is assumed, yes?"
                            if (roll woods_snow_orb orb 60):
                                talk orb talk "<span class='writtenText'>'Air'</span>."
                            else:
                                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            talk sinner talk "And as for the wine... what would I drink instead?"
            talk sinner talk "The Dandelion and Burdock Corporation played a major role in the Die Nam massacre, Cloaca Colo INC in the battle of Gayble Street, but not on the good side. The CEO of Bepis Corp literally just shot a guy in the street once then went back to 'work' with no consequences."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk nasty talk "I kicked a couple of fascist heads in at Gable Street."
                "\\"Oh me oh my, you're quite the working class hero, Nasty Girl.\\"":
                    talk lovely talk "Papi would hate her, titter titter!"
                    clear_dialog
                    talk nasty talk "I'm not fucking <span class='writtenText'>'working'</span> class. I'm fucking scum class, babey. Smelly, fucking, never worked a proper day in her life, nasty class. But my mate Dave *is*."
                    choice:
                        talk nasty talk "It's called solidarity ghost, not that you'd know anything about that you fucking bootlicker."
                        "Hey, I don't lick boots!":
                            run skip
                        "Hey, I only lick boots belonging to particularly scary and attractive women!":
                            run skip
                        "Mmmmm leather yum yum slurp.":
                            run skip
                "\\"No distractions please, Nasty Girl. I want to pay attention to what this lady is saying.\\"":
                    run skip
            clear_dialog
            talk sinner talk "There is no good in this world, Ghost. We paid for those bullets. We are all covered in each other's blood."
            clear_dialog
            "She shakes her head."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk sinner talk "What, pray tell, is the use in worrying about it anymore? When we die none of us are so free of sin as to be spared."
                "\\"I guess you're right. Probably. I don't really understand a lot of what you say, I'll be honest.\\"":
                    talk sinner talk "Then just trust me, Ghost. Come with me and escape the inescapable."
                "\\"Damn. If that's the case I should sin more. I'm going to go buy some Ice Cold Cloaca Colo tm... delicious... yes.... cocaine and sugar... mmm... must have it...\\"":
                    choice:
                        talk sinner talk "You could do that. Or you could come with me. Come with me and escape the inescapable."
                        "\\"Uhhhh. Logical fallacy 🤓. Akshully its impossible to escape an inescapable fate.\\"":
                            choice:
                                talk sinner talk "Stop making that face."
                                "\\"Sorry.\\" [Stop making that face]":
                                    run skip
            clear_dialog
            "She places her hands on your shoulders, leans to your level. Her eyes look into yours. Her nails are sharp. Her grip tight."
            clear_dialog
            talk sinner talk "Perhaps that is what draws me to you, Ghost. I can see it in your eyes."
            talk sinner talk "Innocent. Blank as a babe."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk sinner talk "You have already had a taste of it, that sweet <span class='magenta'>magenta</span>."
                "\\"Maybe a little. It's only been a few days since I got orbed, that's what I call it, orbed, and I already feel pretty grotty again. Like my head is stuffed full of grease form the stove top, spiders and glass.\\" [Shake your head] \\"This world is no place for a lady.\\"":
                    talk orb talk "<span class='writtenText'>'Orbed'</span>?????"
                "\\"Ye.\\"":
                    run skip
                "\\"Eh.\\"":
                    run skip
                "\\"<span class='magenta'>magenta</span>.\\"":
                    talk sinner talk "Oh <span class='magenta'>magenta</span>."
            jump woods_menu
        "\\"I'm sorry you haven't found your cave yet.\\"":
            talk sinner talk "It is what it is. At least we are getting some fresh air, no?"
            clear_dialog
            "She inhales her cigarette fumes. She turns to you, and speaks, uncharacteristically chipper. A bit out of it."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk sinner talk "Listen to the birds, Ghost. Isn't it nice? Their song?"
                "[Listen to the birds]":
                    "The Wood Pigeon above you is making a soft wooing sound. It's enjoying the smoke drifting into its beak. Not far away another Wood Pigeon coos. A sparrow somewhere else, and a kite."
                    choice:
                        "All sing to one another. Friends? Probably not. The Kite would eat them all if it could."
                        "\\"The birds sound nice.\\"":
                            choice:
                                talk sinner talk "Shush. No need for words. Just listen."
                                "[Just listen]":
                                    wait 4000
                        "ADD THIRD CHJOICE HERE.":
                            talk poppy talk "No!"
            jump woods_menu
        "[Sniff]":
            "The Sinner, but beyond her the smell of green, or what was once green. Wet leaves and moss. Ferns on their last legs. They'll be back next year, it's ok. We all have bad seasons."
            jump woods_menu
        "[Lean against The Sinner]":
            play sound clothing
            "She does not move at first, though you feel her eye shift briefly. After a moment she ruffles your hair."
            jump woods_menu
        "[Take in the silence] <span class='prompt'>[[MOVE ON]]</span>" if $data.woods.sinChat:
            jump woods_pit

woods_pit:
    wait 4000
    clear_dialog
    play sound rustle
    choice:
        "Another wood pigeon lands on a tree nearby. It peeps at you, and flutters off along with its now nicotine dependent friend. The canopy rustles, and a dead leaf comes loose and lands on your head."
        "[Turn to The Sinner] \\"Look. I have a hat now.\\"":
            choice:
                talk sinner talk "You already had a hat. I don't think I've ever seen you without one, actually."
                "\\"Berets aren't hats they're accessories, idiot.\\"":
                    talk sinner talk "Sure they are, you little weirdo."
                    choice:
                        "She ruffles your hair. Her touch is muted by your head accessory and leaf hat."
                        "\\"Don't patronise me! I'm scary and mean! Grrr! I'll bite and savage you!\\"":
                            run skip
            clear_dialog
            if (roll woods_cute_lovely lovely 20):
                talk lovely talk "She thinks you're cute."
            else:
                wait 1000
            if (roll woods_push_nasty nasty 20):
                talk nasty talk "She wants to push you against a tree."
            else:
                wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    play sound thud
    stop music
    run transition_pain
    choice:
        "She pushes you against the tree. No. Shoves you. This is not a woman who perform motions as subtle as a push. She is a grimy mass of bone and hormone. She wrestles with your coat like she's tangled in it. Bites you. Two times. Three times. Many times."
        "\\"Squeal!\\"":
            "The Sinner makes a sound somewhere between a breathy laugh and an audible smirk. A claw like hand grabs your hair, and pulls your head backwards. A kiss on your cheek. Your beret somehow stays on."
            if $data.ghost.neckBitten:
                "She stops."
                if (roll woods_bruise_nasty nasty 40):
                    talk nasty talk "She spotted a bruise. The one left behind by The Pulp Writer."
                    talk lovely talk "Gasp! Ghost, you slut!"
                    clear_dialog
                    talk nasty talk "It's okay. She likes a girl with multiple layers of bruising. Bites. Scratch marks. It tells a story, like rings in a tree. Layers of paint on her cards. Venereal diseases on a... well, me."
                    if $data.ghost.sawComet:
                        talk lovely talk "...I- I need to talk to my doctor."
                else:
                    wait 1000
                clear_dialog
                choice:
                    talk sinner talk "Whore."
                    "[Make a gay little whimper]":
                        run skip
                    "[Shrug] \\"You should see the other girl.\\"":
                        run skip
            clear_dialog
            "She strokes your face. Cocks her head. Her nose twitches. She knows your scent. Knows you."
            clear_dialog
            talk sinner talk "It is a relief to find a fellow straggler... I appreciate very much your company, Ghost."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                "Her voice is raspy, excited. This woman cannot stop herself monologuing, not even now."
                "\\"Less talking more kissing please.\\"":
                    "A devious little grin, excitement, perhaps?"
                    if (roll woods_grin_lovely lovely 20):
                        talk lovely talk "A rare emotion for The Sinner."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
                "[Nod] \\"Um, you too, thank youuuuu.\\"":
                    run skip
            clear_dialog
            run transition woods_bite
            run transition_pain
            "She kisses you again, and then she bites your neck. Hard. A little too hard, perhaps. Good."
    clear_dialog
    talk sinner talk "I could bite right through. Kill you here and now. Watch you bleed out on the floor. Would it be a mercy, Ghost? Do you truly feel that you deserve to live?"
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "The melodrama of her statement is muffled by your neck, which she is still biting, but you can just about make her words out."
        "\\"I think I do :)\\"":
            talk sinner talk "Mhm?"
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                "Her jaw squeezes ever so slightly tighter."
                "\\"Eep!\\"":
                    run skip
                "\\"Ow!\\"":
                    run skip
                "\\"Whimper!\\"":
                    run skip
        "\\"Euuugh.\\" [Drool] \\"Yes please mam, kill me.\\" [Make a pleading face and whine] \\"Ooo ooooh ooooh.\\"":
            "The Sinner withdraws slightly."
            if (roll woods_rookie_nasty nasty 40):
                talk nasty talk "Hadn't planned a response to you actually wanting that. Rookie. It's like she's never slept with a trans woman before."
            else:
                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            talk sinner talk "I... I'm not going to kill you. Sorry."
            if (roll woods_kill_nasty nasty 40):
                talk nasty talk "She's a little concerned she might kill you by accident now."
            else:
                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            run transition_pain
            choice:
                "She bites you again, a little softer this time. Two fingers stroke your cheek, press against your lips, and slide into your throat."
                "\\"Herruugh!\\"":
                    clear_dialog
                    talk sinner talk "Tell me Ghost, the coal you buy kills us. When you burn it you doom us further. This is true, no? Murder."
    clear_dialog
    run transition_pain
    choice:
        "A fingernail bumps against the back of your throat. Yowch! Hot!"
        "\\"Mffm. I schupposhe sho?\\"":
            talk sinner talk "And so you acknowledge that it is a sin, yes?"
            talk sinner talk "And yet you do it anyway because of some vague notion that someone else shares more of the blame than you? Tell me, would you extend that sympathy to others, those who might hurt you or yours?"
            choice:
                talk sinner talk "Does the one who produces truncheons and riot shields that break up civil rights protests take no blame in our destruction?"
                "\\"Shey do, yegsshh. Shi'm disherent shough, I need coal to shtay warm.\\"":
                    talk sinner talk "And the... the truncheon man, money to live."
                "\\"Uh. I shon't sknow? Mgggffhh.\\"":
                    talk sinner talk "I do."
                "\\"Shis is a bit shoo shepresshing for me. Sheer up! Maybshe we'll find an shrinteresting bug or shomething. Heunnce shyou're shone biting my neshk and violashing my thwoat, I shmean.\\"":
                    "Her brow visibly furrows. Not visible to you, she's buried in your neck. An shrinteresting bug saw it."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk sinner talk "Fine."
                    if (roll woods_retreat_lovely lovely 20):
                        talk lovely talk "She is disappointed in your retreat. The bickering was just getting good, she thinks."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
        "\\"Hrrgh. I shown't fink sat's shentirelshe fair. Mehhghh!\\"":
            talk sinner talk "I do."
        "[Shake your head solemnly] \\"Hhhgh. Shentropy makes shinners of shush shall. When shall we shtrive heuugh ish towards naught, and all we shreate built shon bones, ish shthere shuch a shing as an shinnocent? Mggfh. The very shair we breatshe shount shis an act of violensh againsht the univershe, shand all who live within shit. UUnngggh. But sho what? All who live within it breathe shount, and sho all who live shithin it sheserve to die.":
            "The bizarre sentence you just rambled seems to make The Sinner incredibly horny, her breathing intensifies, her grip tightens."
    clear_dialog
    if $data.ghost.neckBitten:
        "The Sinner finally stops biting your neck. A bruise left behind, just next to your first. Her fingers slip out of your mouth, covered in drool. She wipes it on your arm."
        clear_dialog
        talk nasty talk "No sight more beautiful than a ladies neck bruised by two different women. They should have sent a poet... which they did, I'm a poet."
        clear_dialog
        talk nasty talk "Black red memory."
        talk nasty talk "Oil paint upon oil painting."
        choice:
            talk nasty talk "Me want cigarette."
            "That was so beautiful, Nasty Girl... what a wonderful haiku... [Wipe a tear from your eye] They should have sent a poet. AHEM. What a nice poem. Line break. I liked that poem. A lot. Line break. What a nice poem.":
                talk nasty talk "Thanks babe."
    else:
        "The Sinner finally stops biting your neck. A bruise left behind. Her fingers slip out of your mouth, covered in drool. She wipes it on your arm."
    if (!= $data.ghost.nightmareSexComment true):
        if (roll woods_pit_sex_nightmare nightmare 40):
            set data.ghost.nightmareSexComment true
            choice:
                talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>This is disgusting, right?</span>" 
                "Sex?":
                    talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>No not sex. Sex is great. WE like SEX. No, we're talking about sex that involves *you*.</span>"
        else:
            wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    run transition woods_pit
    "The tall neurosis scarecrow leans against the tree. She was already taller than you, but being bitten has shrunk you by two percent."
    "One of her hands reaches out and rests on the tree above you. The Sinner glares down at you, she looks deeply evil (hot)."
    "She does not speak, but you can tell what she wants."
    clear_dialog
    "You lean forward, and lick her armpit. It's musky (hot). Smells bad (in a good way (hot)) and hasn't been trimmed (hot)."
    "The Sinner stifles a moan, and presses her armpit into your face."
    clear_dialog
    talk sinner talk "I didn't even tell you to do that. It wasn't even a [Choice]. You just did it. Pervert."
    clear_dialog
    talk nasty talk "FUck yes fyuck yes finally some REAL FUCKING FOOD."
    talk lovely talk "Beastly! Simply perverse! Disgusting!"
    talk lovely talk "I wonder if the stable girl has armpits..."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk sinner talk "Keep going, Ghost. Like you mean it."
        "[Make out with the awful woman's armpit]":
            "You kiss it like it's your wife. Gently at first, but then like a rabid hyena devouring a bowl of meat. The Sinner whines, her grim facade briefly breaking from the sensation."
            "She tastes of sweat. You're drowning in her."
            clear_dialog
            talk sinner talk "Heuuugh."
            clear_dialog
            "Finally, she relents. Your face is no longer buried in her armpit, but you can still feel it. Droplets of sweat cling to your whiskers."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "She spits into your still gawping mouth."
        "[Swallow, obviously]":
            "Tastes like spit. Weirdly dry. Minty. Alcohol."
        roll woods_pit_spit_nasty nasty 60 "[Spit back]":
            success "":
                "The look of shock on The Sinner's face is well worth the future retribution. She looked so nonplused. Fair enough, having your own spit parried and used against you would nonplus the best of us."
                play sound slap
                run transition_pain
                "She wipes the spit from her cheek, onto your own cheek, and then slaps you across the same spot."
            failure: "":
                "She somehow parries you, and the spit goes straight back into your mouth and down your throat."
                "Tastes like spit. Weirdly dry. Minty. Alcohol."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk sinner talk "Now say thank you."
        "\\"Thank you.\\"":
            "<span class='goldItalic'>A smile</span>."
        "[Rub your bruised throat] \\"Yowch! Still preddy sore!\\"":
            play sound slap
            run transition_pain
            "The Sinner slaps you across the cheek."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk sinner talk "I said, <span class='writtenText'>'say thank you''</span>."
                "\\"Thank you.\\""
                    "<span class='goldItalic'>A smile</span>."
                "\\"Yowch!\\"":
                    "Her shoulders sink. You have defeated her."
    clear_dialog
    play music ourlovelyladyverse
    run transition woods_two
    wait 4000
    "You walk for a while. An hour or two, maybe. Time moves queerly in the countryside, and queerer still in the woods. A kaleidoscopic blend of moss, birdsong, dirt paths, fungus and solitude. Eventually though, the trees begin to thin."
    if (roll woods_hair_nightmare nightmare 40):
        talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>Like your hair. lol.</span>"
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    "The surviving Anglian woodland breathes its last breath, before decaying once more into fields. By design or by chance, your walk is concluded. The Sinner seems unhappy with this. She slumps against the fence post. A distant steam train sighs for her."
    "Defeat."
    clear_dialog
    run transition woods_sinner
    choice:
        talk sinner talk "Still nothing... still nothing... Tell me, Ghost, in your time living near the woods, traipsing through them, have you stumbled upon any caves in amongst those trees?"
        "\\"I know where to find a fucked up cave. Her holiness told me. Let me show you where to find the fucked up cave.\\"" if $data.ghost.foundDeepCave:
            "Her eyes glint. It is the first light you have seen in them."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk sinner talk "And you didn't think to tell me before?"
                "[Shrug] \\"You didn't ask. I mostly react to stimuli rather than take action. I'm sort of like a venus flytrap.\\"" if (!= $data.ghost.lobsterGirl true):
                    "The Sinner frowns. She's not overly happy with your excuse."
                "[Shrug] \\"You didn't ask. I mostly react to stimuli rather than take action. I'm sort of like a venus flytrap, or a very passive lobster. I lay at the bottom of the sea... don't come near me or I'll *pinch* you!\\" [Snap your hands open and close to imitate claws]" if (== $data.ghost.lobsterGirl true):
                    "The Sinner frowns. She's not overly happy with your excuse."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk sinner talk "And you will take me there, yes? How exciting. What a clever little rat you are, Ghost..."
                "\\"I'll take you there!\\" [Take her there]":
                    talk sinner talk "How lovely..."
                    clear_dialog
                    "Her voice is like wine, trickled into your ear. Nice?"
                    run transition woods_lamp
                    clear_dialog
                    "She gets a previously hidden object out of her coat. A large metal oil lamp. A memento from the Briargrey mine, is it?"
                    clear_dialog
                    talk sinner talk "Hold this."
                    clear_dialog
                    "A gay little flourish lights the lamp. It's really heavy."
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk sinner talk "That's an open flame. Don't fuck up and set fire to thou or thineself, okay?"
                        "[Nod] \\"I'll do my best mam.\\"":
                            "Her expression does not change, but she smirks."
                        "No promises.":
                            run skip
                    clear_dialog
                    talk sinner talk "Lead the way, Songbird."
                    jump woods_magenta
                "\\"No. Sorry. I didn't really find a fucked up cave. I misspoke. I'm a very stupid little rat...\\" [Shake your head forlornly]":
                    talk sinner talk "I see."
                "\\"I don't think I should tell you about the fucked up cave. I'm pretty sure you're going to end up hurting yourself if I tell you where the fucked up cave is.\\"":
                    "The Sinner growls. Teeth bared. A flash of prehistory in her eye, and then she is back to normal. She was right, before, she *could* kill you, if she wanted to."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk sinner talk "Fine. Have it your way, Ghost."
        "\\"I haven't stumbled on any fucked up caves, no.\\"" if (!= $data.ghost.foundDeepCave true):
            talk sinner talk "A shame."
        "\\"I haven't stumbled on any fucked up caves, no.\\" [Lie]" if $data.ghost.foundDeepCave:
            "The Sinner squints at you."
            if (roll woods_liar_lovely lovely 40):
                talk lovely talk "A pungent scent that overpowers even oestradiol smoke and unwashed clothes. The smell of a little liar."
            talk sinner talk "A shame."
    clear_dialog
    "The Sinner sighs."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk sinner talk "Another time, perhaps. Oblivion must, once more, wait..."
        "\\"Oblivion sounds pretty cool, but you know what's cooler? Going for little walks with women.\\" [Nod your head] \\"Do you want to go for another little walk with me tomorrow?\\"":
            set data.ending.presentSinner true
            add data.dream.womenOptions 1
            choice:
                "The segue seems to stun lock The Sinner for a moment."
                "\\"Is that a yes?\\"":
                    talk sinner talk "Hmm..."
                    clear_dialog
                    "She sighs."
                "[Take advantage of the stun lock and punch her in the tummy, dealing double damage]":
                    "You're too slow. The Sinner grabs your wrist, and twists you into a headlock."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk sinner talk "A walk could be enjoyable, I suppose... oblivion can wait a few more days, one supposes..."
        "[Do a gay little smile]":
            if (&& (== $data.sinner.reading "hrt") (!= (has_item? hrt) true)):
                choice:
                    talk sinner talk "The other day you asked about hormones, didn't you, Ghost? You sought knowledge from the cards."
                    "\\"I might have done. I'll be honest my memory is pretty goofy.\\"":
                        talk sinner talk "Lunden Road. Sundown. The moon shall guide your way."
                        clear_dialog
                        "She peers down at you, and cocks her head."
                        clear_dialog
                        choice:
                            talk sinner talk "The Pale Spectre hath spoketh. The Moon cometh. The cards never deceive."
                            "\\"Oh. I already knew that. Thanks though.\\"" if (objective_started? hrt dealer):
                                "The Sinner looks a little upset."
                                if (roll woods_pit_useful_lovely lovely 40):
                                    talk lovely talk "<span class='writtenText'>'I really am useless, aren't I?'</span>"
                                else:
                                    wait 1000
                            "[Nod] \\"Okay. I follow\\"" if (!= (objective_started? hrt dealer) true):
                                start_objective hrt dealer
                                run skip
                            "[Nod] \\"Okay. I follow.\\" Orb, Lovely Lady, Nasty Girl, I don't follow." if (!= (objective_started? hrt dealer) true):
                                choice:
                                    talk orb talk "There's a dealer there, you might be able to get hormones off of her."
                                    "[Nod] I follow.":
                                        run skip
                                    "[Nod] I follow. Lovely Lady, Nasty Girl, I don't follow.":
                                        choice:
                                            talk lovely talk "A spirit of the moon descends on the darkest nights to bring gifts of moondust."
                                            "Oh! Well why didn't everyone just say. [Roll your eyes]":
                                                "The Sinner frowns, watching you emote to yourself and mutter under your breath."
                                                clear_dialog
                                                talk sinner talk "Are you having a stroke? Whatever, it's your right."
                                start_objective hrt dealer
    clear_dialog
    "The Sinner shivers. It is chilly out, and she is very thin. Still, she manages a small <span class='goldItalic'>smile</span> back."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk sinner talk "Tomorrow, Ghost. I will see you again."
        "\\"See you then bestie!\\" <span class='prompt'>[[CONTINUE]]</span>":
            play sound spendAction
    stop ambient 1
    complete_objective sinner woods  
    complete_quest sinner sinnerSuccess
    jump goToGameMap

woods_magenta:
    set data.sinner.wentToCave true
    clear_dialog
    run transition woods_two
    choice:
        "It is as her holiness said. You find the cave. The Sinner does not wait for you. She rushes inside."
        "[Follow her]":
            stop ambient 1
            stop music
            play ambient amb_cave_deep 2
            play ambient magenta 3
            run transition cave_magenta
            "It feels odd. Save the flame dancing in your lamp, there is no light in this cave. There is nothing. It is not a place fit for mammals. It is not a place fit for reptiles. It is not a place. There is a queer smell to it. It smells of magenta."
            "The cave, it appears, continues for some way past this point. It continues for a long, long way, actually."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "It smells of <span class='magenta'>magenta</span>."
        "[Shiver]":
            talk lovely talk "Brr!"
            talk orb talk "Hmm. Same. Let's turn back."
            if (roll magenta_nightmare nightmare 60):
                talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>We all take this path one day, Ghost.</span>"
            else:
                wait 1000
        "[Don't]":      
            if (roll magenta_darkness_nightmare nightmare 20):
                talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>Just because you deny that something is there, doesn't mean it isn't. The thing behind the shelf will wait for you.</span>" 
            else:
                wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    talk lovely talk "Oh me oh my! Ghost, darling, let us depart from this frightful place at once. My nerves are positively shattered!"
    talk orb talk "I... I admit I'm surprised we actually found something, but I'm inclined to agree with Lovely Lady, Ghost. Let's leave, okay?"
    run transition cave_lake
    clear_dialog
    "The Sinner is not far ahead. She stands in a lake of inch deep water. A tear rolls down her cheek. Falls below, deep below. The shallow lake drops off into a deep *deep* well. She stares downwards, deep downwards, deep down to something below."
    "Something brilliant and bright. Like blood shining in moon light on the street. Drenched and congealed in your sheets."
    clear_dialog
    play ambient magenta_two 4
    choice:
        "Ah <span class='magenta'>Magenta</span>..."
        "\\"Ahhhh... <span class='magenta'>Magenta O' magenta</span>...\\"":
            "<span class='magenta'>THE WRITHING BEFITS THEE NOT?</span>"
    set data.ghost.knowsDreamer true
    unlock_achievement magenta
    "<span class='magenta'>THAT IS OF NO SURPRISE. THERE IS NO FUTURE WORTH DECAYING EVER ON FOR. THERE IS ONLY NOW. NOW, THE WRITHING AND THE TIME AFTER. WHEN THE ANGELS FALL AND THE DREAM IS OVER. THE TIME BETWEEN IS THUS. THE EVILS OF YOUR KIND HAVE KILLED ALL ELSE. CAPITAL HAS KILLED ALL ELSE. ALL FUTURES. ALL BELIEFS. ALL DREAMS. YOUR KIND HAS BIRTHED ANGELS MORE GREAT AND TERRIBLE EVEN THAN THE ROTTING SPIRE. THAN THE NIGHTMARES THAT SING IN THE CLOUDS. YOUR IDEOLOGIES AND ALL THEIR ARMIES. YOU SEE THIS DO, YOU NOT? THE DREAM HAS BECOME STALE. ROTTEN. WHAT CRUEL GOD WOULD DREAM A WORLD SO? WHAT CRUEL GOD WOULD DREAM YOU INTO THIS VICIOUSNESS OUT OF IGNORANCE?"
    clear_dialog
